import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['net_generation'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of net generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    data.boxplot(column='net_generation', by='source', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of net generation by source?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Source')
    ax.set_ylabel('Net Generation')
    ax.axhline(y=data['net_generation'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['net_generation'].median()))
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    df = data.groupby('source')['net_generation'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.bar(df['source'], df['net_generation'])
    plt.title('What is the average net generation by source?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Average net generation')
    plt.xlabel('Source')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['year'], data['net_generation'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Net Generation')
    ax.set_title('What is the correlation between net generation and year?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['net_generation'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['net_generation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['net_generation'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of net generation?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
